HEADWORD: Sutor
<hw>Su"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of sirup made by
the Indians of Arizona from the fruit of some cactaceous plant (probably
the <xex>Cereus giganteus</xex>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

